remarks.para:
However, if a sub-type is not supported by Hodoku (e.g. the field
), this method will still return 
indicating the "Not supported" state.

param.para:
All available  results will be stored in property 
of this argument, if property  returns ;
otherwise, the property won't be used, and this method will return the first found step.

remarks.para:
The recommended implementation pattern is:

private string CellsStr => Cells.ToString();
private string DigitsStr => Digits.ToString(separator: R.EmitPunctuation(Punctuation.Comma));

And then fill the blank via property :
public override IDictionary<string, string[]?> FormatInterpolatedParts => [["en-US": [CellsStr, DigitsStr]], ["zh-CN": [CellsStr, DigitsStr]]];
via the feature "Collection Literals" introduced in C# 12. If you cannot decide the real name of the culture name, just use suffix instead like "en" and "zh", ignoring cases.

If you want to use the values in the resource dictionary, you can just use a  field
called , for example:

using static Sudoku.Resources.MergedResources;

public override string Format => R["TheKeyYouWantToSearch"];
